# Sample env template for the shop exemplar.
#
# These keys map to the test accounts documented in hints/forge.md. Copy
# this file to `.env` (gitignored), fill in the actual values from the
# demo's official docs, and either:
#
#   - uncomment `import 'dotenv/config'` in playwright.config.ts to have
#     forge load this file on each spec run, OR
#   - leave dotenv commented out and load the same keys via direnv,
#     dotenv-cli, manual shell exports, or your secrets manager.
#
# Forge takes no opinion on how values reach process.env; it just expects
# them to be there when the driver runs.
#
# The placeholders below are intentionally not real credentials. Even
# publicly-documented demo creds shouldn't sit in a tracked file — the
# exemplar follows the same env-hygiene rule it teaches.

# --- customer (standard test account) ---
PST_CUSTOMER_EMAIL=
PST_CUSTOMER_PASSWORD=

# --- customer2 (second seat for parallel runs) ---
PST_CUSTOMER2_EMAIL=
PST_CUSTOMER2_PASSWORD=

# --- admin (admin dashboard, exempt from account-lockout) ---
PST_ADMIN_EMAIL=
PST_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
